reviews.title: The prices of the site are different than on the menu.This is confusing and not fun.
reviews.text:
Cozy restaurant but take a good look at which menu you ordered, which we mistook for a plate of €19.75 turned out to be more expensive, namely €24.75. This because it turned out to be a main menu. Next to us people ordered a plate of kibbeling with a basket of Fries and salad which we have not seen on the menu. Chicken nuggets and a frikandel were also ordered from another table. Had we known this, the choice for us would have gone to the quibble, etc.
Furthermore, the food was tasty and not salty, which benefits the taste.

reviews.title: It's worth repeating!!👍👍
reviews.text:
Deliciously varied lunch

High sea, diamond hare, schnitzel and kids box.  Lovely, nicely made up. Very friendly service.

tips.body: Geniet. Is gezellig. En vandaag levendig. Prima!

reviews.title: Disappointed.
reviews.text:
The expectations were quite high considering the 4.4 review unfortunately those expectations were not met the starter fried large shrimp was ok the main course according to the card consisted of varia fish -4 species- on our plate 3 types 1 lean tongue , 1 plaice and a piece of fried with salad beans and fries.....so nothing special far from it. The disappointment was great we didn't even take dessert.
Unbelievable noise in the restaurant which is difficult for less mobile people to reach given the stairs to it

tips.body: Wij zouden niet meer dit restaurant kiezen

reviews.title: No allergen list, not welcoming
reviews.text:
The day before our visit to Urk the choice fell on this beautifully located restaurant with a number of dishes on the menu that were allowed because of food allergies. 

After a bike ride on the terrace to find out that they did not have a (mandatory) allergen card nor they knew what was in the products (read) dishes and it seemed as if they certainly did not care.
Unfortunately we have to leave and around the corner at the Urk Vishal (chip shop for fish) eat kibbeling because they know what they are doing and are doing.
What a mockery is The Seabed on Urk.

reviews.title: Ariel with Allergies on the seabed can land you if you don't pay attention.

reviews.title: Good food, noisy company,
reviews.text: The food was fine, (too) generous portions with three-course menu. The service was good, just not well matched. So they came twice in a row asking for drinking or. What was annoying was that there was a large noisy company that made sure we left as soon as possible after dessert. Too bad!

reviews.title: Delicious lunch
reviews.text: Delicious lunch! Delicious kibbeling and a very tasty salad with smoked fish. Very friendly service, nice view from our (vooaf reserved) table on the harbor. We will definitely be back here!

reviews.title: Super
reviews.text: Delicious food. The bickering was really super tasty. The atmosphere and service was also good Nice view of the port of Urk.

reviews.title: Nice location and delicious lunch
reviews.text: Had a lovely lunch. Friendly staff and nice views of the harbor. Nothing to add and worth repeating

reviews.title: Urk hospitality a big 10!!
reviews.text: Ended up here via Tripadvisor, had a delicious lunch, where an Italian roll of smoked salmon was filled with salmon in such a way that you had to look for the Italian roll and believe me it is the other way around for many things. Super friendly, nice young girls serving, in Urk they know how to receive your guests.

reviews.title: Recommended
reviews.text: We particularly enjoyed the fish specialties on the etagere with spiced potato dippers. You'll eat your fingers with it, it's so delicious. The service also deserves praise. Definitely recommended and worth repeating

reviews.title: An innovative dish!  High tea for fish!
reviews.text: Saw this on customers tables when passing and persuaded us to enter and order same!  Excellent choice for lunch, dinner or even mid afternoon.  Inexpensive too and restaurant is right on quayside. Good location to watch harbour in the sun for

reviews.title: Excellent seafood restaurant
reviews.text:
Really delicious fresh seafood with delicious salads & very tasty french fries. We bought extra fried cod bits for our evening meal at home, also a half of their delicious home smoked salmon.
The restaurant is situated in the harbour with glorious views.

reviews.title: Pleasant atmosphere ,nice restaurant near the harbour
reviews.text: I was in Urk with my Dutch  family for the second time ,we decided to try their fish for the first time ,in a restaurant which was in front of the harbour .They ordered a special dish called'' Plate Urk met schol en tong''...The waitress told me in English that it was a kind of flatfish ,the price was 19.25 euro .She brought to me  a big plate with two different fish ,a salad and chips.The fish was tasty ,but I didn't have a special knife for selecting the bones , after dinner my plate looked awful ..Anyway ,I was not very happy with the  selection of fish I ordered .

I tasted the nice picture of the harbour from the terrace outside

reviews.title: Very good food, nice staff!
reviews.text: Beautiful place at the harbor. I took the menu. Shrimps from the grill, roast rib in red wine sauce and a tropical dessert. Everything absolutely nice and worth the money. The fish soup is nice as well. Will certainly come back!

seoInfo.metaDescription: Traveling with your dog has never been easier—or more fun. Cities across the country boast pet-friendly hotels, parks, and activities. Whether it’s a quick getaway or a bucket-list trip, our guides help you stay, play, and explore with your pup. Grab the leash and go!

tripContent.title: Experience Santa Fe: art, flavor & fun on the Original Route 66
tripContent.description: Whether you enjoy nature hikes or margarita trails (or both!), you'll want to embrace everything Santa Fe has to offer. Its unique mix of big-city culture, small-town charm, and Southwestern flavor has earned it the nickname "The City Different." Whatever you're into—from art to opera to world-class restaurants—Santa Fe offers a chance to escape the everyday.

articleContent.title: 12 hotels in Paris with the best Eiffel Tower views

seoInfo.metaDescription: Where to stay in Paris for the best Eiffel Tower views—no matter your budget—according to reviews from Tripadvisor travelers.

They say two is better than one—and in Ixtapa-Zihuatanejo, that couldn’t be more true. Ixtapa is modern and vibrant, with luxury resorts, breathtaking views, and settings surrounded by lush tropical nature. Zihuatanejo, a Pueblo Mágico, offers cobblestone streets, deep-rooted traditions, and a laid-back coastal vibe. Together, they deliver a travel experience that’s as diverse as it is authentic—earning Ixtapa-Zihuatanejo its place among Mexico’s top beach destinations.

Though some people swear it can’t be done, I’m here to tell you it’s possible to see Florence in just one day. I’ve whittled down my go-to itinerary to just the essentials. You won’t have time to linger too long in any one place, so drink in the views—of the Arno River from the Ponte Vecchio or the city skyline from the Piazzale Michelangelo—and keep moving. It was tough leaving out some of my personal favorites like the Basilica of Santa Croce, so promise me you’ll add them to your list for your return visit. And yes, I guarantee you’ll be coming back once you get a taste of everything Florence has to offer.

reviews.title: Worth the wait
reviews.text: We had a light lunch here and were pleasantly surprised. We ordered the High Sea (to share) - a different take on the High Tea. A selection of freshly prepared fresh produce - in our case fish & seafood. We can highly recommend this dish. It took a while but was certainly worth the wait.

reviews.title: Pleasant, reasonable priced lunch + 'Religeous Sermon'
reviews.text:
My wife enjoyed her tasty Mosselen meal.  I had cod kibbling with fries and salad.   Pleasant waitress service to table with view over harbour and boats.  Good value.
Adjacent to us was a film crew recording a script by a young man, firstly in Dutch or maybe German and then in English.  This is when we heard that the shoot was recording a themed promotion or plea for donations for a religeous cause!  The script described how Jesus divided the 5 loaves and 2 fishes to feed the multitude of his followers.
We found this experience incongruous to film it in a quality restaurant filled with diners feeding themselves with plentiful  plates of food!!!

reviews.title: Food View and Services
reviews.text: We were there on Monday evening and it was not busy. The view also very nice but after sunset. 5 of us enjoyed the food very much. The waitress was attentive and lovely.

reviews.title: BUSY HARBOUR-SIDE RESTAURANT - EXCELLENT VALUE
reviews.text:
Late lunch for two on a Saturday, was a delight. The soups are excellent as in the bread platter. The dish of the day offers real value. We decided on the 3 course, set lunch, but could not manage a desert. Be careful because you still have to pay for it, so go easy on the bread, unless you're quite hungry.

Service was good and efficient, but not outstanding.

reviews.title: Nice meal with a nice view
reviews.text: We had a quick lunch at the Zeebodem: a panini chicken thighs, a panini smoked salmon, a child's menu and a 'plate Urk'. It was all very tasty, really value for money. Service was good and very friendly. Would definitely go back for lunch again.

reviews.title: Good meal despite the wasps
reviews.text:
A group of us ate here with work last week and were treated to a reasonable spread. The food was good, no more than that. One very measerly portion of chips between the four of us ( we were offered more and they arrived 15minutes later when we had finished our meal). 

Very nice setting out on the harbour front and the food was generally very tasty. 

There was annoying amount of wasps too which were not been dealt with really either.  A few more deterrents would have been ideal.

reviews.title: Excellent food and service and really good value
reviews.text:
We had the three course option from the a la carte menu for 25 Euros and it was very very good with high quality ingredients, well cooked and presented. The shrimp starter with apple and mango was a revelation. The steak was sublime. And the fish soup wonderful - excellent fish and seafood with a rich asparagus soup.
The carpaccio of beetroot was unusual and very tasty; the salmon with popcorn quinoa was fantastic.
And all substantial portions.

reviews.title: Nice food, I'd worry if it was busy!
reviews.text:
I stopped here for a spot of lunch, I was the only person in the place and the service was a little slow. 

The service was the mediocre, but the food was great. I had the fish soup, which was really nicely presented - seafood in the bottom of the bowl and a jug of soup poured over it, it tasted great.

I then had the Zeebodem fish platter, which was two flatfish, salad and a load of chips. Both were really well cooked and the Sole was lovely but the Plaice not very tasty, I'm not sure if that was down to the cooking or the fish! There was so much food, I didn't need the salad although it did look really nice.

The restaurant is overlooking the harbour and in summer or on a sunny day I think it would be lovely. I'd go back.

reviews.title: Great (sea)food for little money
reviews.text:
We had an excellent dinner here and were treated to some of the best fish we ever had. Appetiser, mains and dessert for 25 Euros per person! 
Delicious, good portions, a nicely decorated restaurant with friendly staff

reviews.title: Fresh fish and great view
reviews.text: We had been to "Zeebodem" before, and as we happened to be in Urk again, decided to re-visit for lunch. If you want delicious freshly-cooked fish, choose "kibbeling met remoulade saus". Pieces of battered cod, with crinkly chips and salad. A massive plateful of good quality food, and for only € 10,- very good value for money. And all with a beautiful view over the harbour!

reviews.title: No Irk in Urk
reviews.text: We enjoyed a lovely lunch in Urk at Zeebodem restaurant. The food was very good and so was the beer. We had a table overlooking the harbour. The staff were very attentive and friendly. We were certainly not irked in Urk. Nice visit. Take a walk up the hill to see the Memoriam to some 200 plus fishermen who died at sea over the past 400 years.

reviews.title: Dutch seafood – very good!
reviews.text: We enjoyed a nice lunch at Zeebodem: Dutch seafood both in the form of "kibbeling" (deep-friend fish pieces with remoulade sauce) and a superb salad with smoked fish & eel. The terrace has great views over the old fishing harbour and the staff is friendly. Good option along the waterfront.
